until a group is exhausted.

53:10.000 --> 53:12.000
If it's 7 minutes,

53:12.000 --> 53:14.000
the group starts to exhale,

53:14.000 --> 53:16.000
trying to warm it up.

53:16.000 --> 53:18.000
But within 15-20 minutes,

53:18.000 --> 53:20.000
the group usually exhales

53:20.000 --> 53:22.000
and stops generating ideas.

53:22.000 --> 53:24.000
At this stage,

53:24.000 --> 53:26.000
the group's work stops.

53:26.000 --> 53:28.000
The group is thanked

53:28.000 --> 53:30.000
for its creative participation

53:30.000 --> 53:32.000
in solving the problem.

53:32.000 --> 53:34.000
Moreover, even non-professionals

53:34.000 --> 53:36.000
can generate ideas

53:36.000 --> 53:38.000
and pass them on to other groups.

53:38.000 --> 53:40.000
And this is where

53:40.000 --> 53:42.000
the work begins.

53:42.000 --> 53:44.000
An example of this

53:44.000 --> 53:46.000
use of brainstorming

53:46.000 --> 53:48.000
can be an interesting operation.

53:48.000 --> 53:50.000
An interesting situation.

53:50.000 --> 53:52.000
We know that there was

53:52.000 --> 53:54.000
the Great Patriotic War

53:54.000 --> 53:56.000
during the World War.

53:56.000 --> 53:58.000
Germany, for the first time

53:58.000 --> 54:00.000
in the history of mankind,

54:00.000 --> 54:02.000
invented

54:02.000 --> 54:04.000
underwater torpedoes

54:04.000 --> 54:06.000
that were launched

54:06.000 --> 54:08.000
from the bottom of the class

54:08.000 --> 54:10.000
by the water.

54:10.000 --> 54:12.000
They were launched by the water,

54:12.000 --> 54:14.000
and reached the target.

54:14.000 --> 54:16.000
They were designed

54:16.000 --> 54:18.000
primarily for the enemy's submarines.

54:18.000 --> 54:20.000
Germany destroyed

54:20.000 --> 54:22.000
the British fleet first.

54:24.000 --> 54:26.000
The torpedo was launched.

54:26.000 --> 54:28.000
It was discovered very late,

54:28.000 --> 54:30.000
when the submarine,

54:30.000 --> 54:32.000
having a lot of weight,

54:32.000 --> 54:34.000
had to be protected.

54:34.000 --> 54:36.000
The British Navy

54:36.000 --> 54:38.000
gathered officers,

54:38.000 --> 54:40.000
including non-professionals,

54:40.000 --> 54:42.000
and started thinking

54:42.000 --> 54:44.000
what to do.

54:44.000 --> 54:46.000
They generated ideas.

54:46.000 --> 54:48.000
When the ideas

54:48.000 --> 54:50.000
at the stage of mass generation

54:50.000 --> 54:52.000
were coming to an end,

54:52.000 --> 54:54.000
they decided to speed up the situation.

54:54.000 --> 54:56.000
They said,

54:56.000 --> 54:58.000
you officers are waiting

54:58.000 --> 55:00.000
on the bridge,

55:00.000 --> 55:02.000
and you are 5 meters away

55:02.000 --> 55:04.000
from the submarine.

55:04.000 --> 55:06.000
What to do?

55:06.000 --> 55:08.000
The officers and the submarines

55:08.000 --> 55:10.000
wanted to live.

55:10.000 --> 55:12.000
One of them said,

55:12.000 --> 55:14.000
I don't care about your tasks.

55:14.000 --> 55:16.000
The neighbor said,

55:16.000 --> 55:18.000
I don't care.

55:18.000 --> 55:20.000
We will launch a single shot

55:20.000 --> 55:22.000
at the enemy's torpedo.

55:22.000 --> 55:24.000
The water splashes out,

55:24.000 --> 55:26.000
the torpedo is thrown up,

55:26.000 --> 55:28.000
the direction changes,

55:28.000 --> 55:30.000
and the torpedo passes

55:30.000 --> 55:32.000
above the submarine.

55:32.000 --> 55:34.000
Or below.

55:34.000 --> 55:36.000
The direction of movement changes.

55:36.000 --> 55:38.000
That's it. The solution was found.

55:38.000 --> 55:40.000
It was a simple and effective solution,

55:40.000 --> 55:42.000
although it was difficult

55:42.000 --> 55:44.000
to come up with something.

55:44.000 --> 55:46.000
I would like to say

55:46.000 --> 55:48.000
that after listening to this course,

55:48.000 --> 55:50.000
and looking at the electronic textbook,

55:50.000 --> 55:52.000
we have some skills left,

55:52.000 --> 55:54.000
some tools to solve problems.

55:54.000 --> 55:56.000
And since any person

55:56.000 --> 55:58.000
who starts his career

55:58.000 --> 56:00.000
as a first-line manager

56:00.000 --> 56:02.000
strives to reach the top,

56:02.000 --> 56:04.000
we will look at what is useful

56:04.000 --> 56:06.000
at all levels.

56:06.000 --> 56:08.000
And now let's look

56:08.000 --> 56:10.000
at the important points

56:10.000 --> 56:12.000
in organizing a brainstorming,

56:12.000 --> 56:14.000
which help to organize it

56:14.000 --> 56:16.000
in your company.

56:16.000 --> 56:18.000
First of all,

56:18.000 --> 56:20.000
there are many questions,

56:20.000 --> 56:22.000
including,

56:22.000 --> 56:24.000
it seems,

56:24.000 --> 56:26.000
that it is necessary to have

56:26.000 --> 56:28.000
some qualities to lead

56:28.000 --> 56:30.000
a brainstorming.

56:30.000 --> 56:32.000
No, no such qualities

56:32.000 --> 56:34.000
are required.

56:34.000 --> 56:36.000
You just need to know how to use technology.

56:36.000 --> 56:38.000
When we come to the doctor

56:38.000 --> 56:40.000
to treat a tooth,

56:40.000 --> 56:42.000
we demand leadership qualities from him.

56:42.000 --> 56:44.000
No, he can drill, find,

56:44.000 --> 56:46.000
put a seal,

56:46.000 --> 56:48.000
and nothing else is required.

56:48.000 --> 56:50.000
So, when organizing a brainstorming,

56:50.000 --> 56:52.000
no special qualities are required.

56:52.000 --> 56:54.000
You just need to know how to select

56:54.000 --> 56:56.000
a group of idea generators,

56:56.000 --> 56:58.000
which will perform two stages,

56:58.000 --> 57:00.000
scouting generation

57:00.000 --> 57:02.000
and cascade idea generation.

57:02.000 --> 57:04.000
That's all.

57:04.000 --> 57:06.000
You just need to know how to select

57:06.000 --> 57:08.000
people with creative abilities.

57:08.000 --> 57:10.000
How do they select?

57:10.000 --> 57:12.000
They are selected by tests.

57:12.000 --> 57:14.000
There is a simple test

57:14.000 --> 57:16.000
for the dominant type of thinking,

57:16.000 --> 57:18.000
that is, for right-left half-circle.

57:18.000 --> 57:20.000
Faces with a pronounced

57:20.000 --> 57:22.000
right-left half-circle

57:22.000 --> 57:24.000
are the dominant type of thinking.

57:24.000 --> 57:26.000
Logicians, those who work

57:26.000 --> 57:28.000
more with a left-half-circle,

57:28.000 --> 57:30.000
are better not to invite

57:30.000 --> 57:32.000
to the group of idea generators.

57:32.000 --> 57:34.000
What is required?

57:34.000 --> 57:36.000
After setting the task,

57:36.000 --> 57:38.000
you need to ensure

57:38.000 --> 57:40.000
one simple rule

57:40.000 --> 57:42.000
that no ideas are criticized.

57:42.000 --> 57:44.000
All ideas are announced

57:44.000 --> 57:46.000
and new ideas

57:46.000 --> 57:48.000
should arise

57:48.000 --> 57:50.000
in the group of idea generators.

57:50.000 --> 57:52.000
It is not necessary

57:52.000 --> 57:54.000
to fix a specific idea.

57:54.000 --> 57:56.000
Each idea is fixed

57:56.000 --> 57:58.000
and recorded on a piece of paper.

57:58.000 --> 58:00.000
The paper is handed over

58:00.000 --> 58:02.000
to the group number 2

58:02.000 --> 58:04.000
after both stages of idea generation.

58:04.000 --> 58:06.000
All ideas,

58:06.000 --> 58:08.000
110, 112, 170,

58:08.000 --> 58:10.000
are handed over to the group number 2.

58:10.000 --> 58:12.000
That's all.

58:12.000 --> 58:14.000
We do not criticize anyone.

58:14.000 --> 58:16.000
We encourage new statements.

58:16.000 --> 58:18.000
New ideas.

58:18.000 --> 58:20.000
In the first group,

58:20.000 --> 58:22.000
ideas are not criticized,

58:22.000 --> 58:24.000
but any, even the most fantastic ideas

58:24.000 --> 58:26.000
are encouraged.

58:26.000 --> 58:28.000
They are welcomed.

58:28.000 --> 58:30.000
As many as you want.

58:30.000 --> 58:32.000
Any most unrealistic ideas,

58:32.000 --> 58:34.000
even to do something

58:34.000 --> 58:36.000
with a phantom reflector or a disintegrator.

58:36.000 --> 58:38.000
There are no disintegrators yet.

58:38.000 --> 58:40.000
They are handed over to the group number 2.

58:40.000 --> 58:42.000
After that,

58:42.000 --> 58:44.000
they work there.

58:44.000 --> 58:46.000
In the first part,

58:46.000 --> 58:48.000
the ideas are not signed

58:48.000 --> 58:50.000
by the author.

58:50.000 --> 58:52.000
They are considered

58:52.000 --> 58:54.000
a product of the collegial generation.

58:54.000 --> 58:56.000
The group,

58:56.000 --> 58:58.000
which produced

58:58.000 --> 59:00.000
the ideas one by one,

59:00.000 --> 59:02.000
without the authorship of the ideas,

59:02.000 --> 59:04.000
is sent to the next group.

59:04.000 --> 59:06.000
There they are divided

59:06.000 --> 59:08.000
into three baskets.

59:08.000 --> 59:10.000
We usually have a ballot box.

59:10.000 --> 59:12.000
Or we call them differently.

59:12.000 --> 59:14.000
In one basket,

59:14.000 --> 59:16.000
unrealizable ideas are put together.

59:20.000 --> 59:22.000
Out of these 170 proposals,

59:22.000 --> 59:24.000
a whole bunch of them.

59:26.000 --> 59:28.000
In the other basket,

59:28.000 --> 59:30.000
realizable ideas are put together.

59:32.000 --> 59:34.000
And in the third basket,

59:34.000 --> 59:36.000
potentially realizable ideas.

59:36.000 --> 59:38.000
Ideas that can be realized

59:38.000 --> 59:40.000
when resources or technology

59:40.000 --> 59:42.000
are used.

59:42.000 --> 59:44.000
For example,

59:44.000 --> 59:46.000
the press has reported

59:46.000 --> 59:48.000
that Siemens

59:48.000 --> 59:50.000
has made

59:50.000 --> 59:52.000
a folding display

59:52.000 --> 59:54.000
with a size

59:54.000 --> 59:56.000
of a notebook.

59:58.000 --> 01:00:00.000
Unfortunately,

01:00:00.000 --> 01:00:02.000
the developers

01:00:02.000 --> 01:00:04.000
can see

01:00:04.000 --> 01:00:06.000
four shades of gray on it.

01:00:06.000 --> 01:00:08.000
They want to make it colorful.

01:00:08.000 --> 01:00:10.000
What are these displays for?

01:00:10.000 --> 01:00:12.000
They should be connected

01:00:12.000 --> 01:00:14.000
to mobile phones.

01:00:14.000 --> 01:00:16.000
We have a phone with an Internet output,

01:00:16.000 --> 01:00:18.000
small calculators, processors.

01:00:18.000 --> 01:00:20.000
They make the keyboard

01:00:20.000 --> 01:00:22.000
to the mobile phone.

01:00:22.000 --> 01:00:24.000
To get rid of computers in life,

01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:26.000
not to carry laptops,

01:00:26.000 --> 01:00:28.000
not to have computers at home.

01:00:28.000 --> 01:00:30.000
Computers are considered

01:00:30.000 --> 01:00:32.000
as a dying generation of technology.

01:00:32.000 --> 01:00:34.000
We need screens.

01:00:34.000 --> 01:00:36.000
We take a pocket screen,

01:00:36.000 --> 01:00:38.000
edit the text,

01:00:38.000 --> 01:00:40.000
send it to someone

01:00:40.000 --> 01:00:42.000
or connect

01:00:42.000 --> 01:00:44.000
a printing device

01:00:44.000 --> 01:00:46.000
and print the text.

01:00:50.000 --> 01:00:52.000
The decision,

01:00:52.000 --> 01:00:54.000
the principal decision,

01:00:54.000 --> 01:00:56.000
is to make such

01:00:56.000 --> 01:00:58.000
folding displays.

01:00:58.000 --> 01:01:00.000
The technical decision

01:01:00.000 --> 01:01:02.000
does not allow

01:01:02.000 --> 01:01:04.000
mass production.

01:01:04.000 --> 01:01:06.000
The decision about the creation

01:01:06.000 --> 01:01:08.000
of such a display

01:01:08.000 --> 01:01:10.000
is put in a folder

01:01:10.000 --> 01:01:12.000
with potential solutions.

01:01:14.000 --> 01:01:16.000
The solutions that are not realized

01:01:16.000 --> 01:01:18.000
are excluded from the review.

01:01:18.000 --> 01:01:20.000
The third group

01:01:20.000 --> 01:01:22.000
is given

01:01:22.000 --> 01:01:24.000
the solutions that are realized

01:01:24.000 --> 01:01:26.000
today.

01:01:26.000 --> 01:01:28.000
The group of analysts

01:01:28.000 --> 01:01:30.000
considers

01:01:30.000 --> 01:01:32.000
how these solutions

01:01:32.000 --> 01:01:34.000
should be provided,

01:01:34.000 --> 01:01:36.000
calculates them,

01:01:36.000 --> 01:01:38.000
to develop the basic options,

01:01:38.000 --> 01:01:40.000
including the use of mathematical methods

01:01:40.000 --> 01:01:42.000
to further

01:01:42.000 --> 01:01:44.000
implement this decision.

01:01:44.000 --> 01:01:46.000
Potentially, the implementation of the solution

01:01:46.000 --> 01:01:48.000
is also considered by other groups,

01:01:48.000 --> 01:01:50.000
since they are not relevant

01:01:50.000 --> 01:01:52.000
at the moment.

01:01:52.000 --> 01:01:54.000
These are the possible options

01:01:54.000 --> 01:01:56.000
of the management decision,

01:01:56.000 --> 01:01:58.000
which are not urgent.

01:01:58.000 --> 01:02:00.000
I hope it is clear now

01:02:00.000 --> 01:02:02.000
that the company does not invite

01:02:02.000 --> 01:02:04.000
specialists of game engineering,

01:02:04.000 --> 01:02:06.000
who can easily organize

01:02:06.000 --> 01:02:08.000
such interesting events.

01:02:10.000 --> 01:02:12.000
The whole brainstorming

01:02:12.000 --> 01:02:14.000
takes 1-2 hours

01:02:14.000 --> 01:02:16.000
of astronomical time.

01:02:20.000 --> 01:02:22.000
The next very interesting method

01:02:24.000 --> 01:02:26.000
that is in the group

01:02:26.000 --> 01:02:28.000
of creative methods

01:02:28.000 --> 01:02:30.000
of decision-making

01:02:30.000 --> 01:02:32.000
is a meeting.

01:02:32.000 --> 01:02:34.000
It is easy and difficult at the same time.

01:02:34.000 --> 01:02:36.000
Why is it easy?

01:02:36.000 --> 01:02:38.000
Because every day,

01:02:38.000 --> 01:02:40.000
every week, our managers

01:02:40.000 --> 01:02:42.000
hold some meetings.

01:02:44.000 --> 01:02:46.000
The difficulty is that we are used to them

01:02:46.000 --> 01:02:48.000
and we make a lot of mistakes

01:02:48.000 --> 01:02:50.000
that

01:02:50.000 --> 01:02:52.000
sharply reduce the efficiency

01:02:52.000 --> 01:02:54.000
of management activity.

01:02:54.000 --> 01:02:56.000
Mistakes in holding meetings.

01:02:56.000 --> 01:02:58.000
I had to configure the meeting system

01:02:58.000 --> 01:03:00.000
in one Russian company

01:03:00.000 --> 01:03:02.000
of the pro-Western type.

01:03:02.000 --> 01:03:04.000
First, I held the meeting

01:03:04.000 --> 01:03:06.000
myself,

01:03:06.000 --> 01:03:08.000
working as a head of the internal training service.

01:03:08.000 --> 01:03:10.000
Secondly,

01:03:10.000 --> 01:03:12.000
since I already had experience

01:03:12.000 --> 01:03:14.000
in holding meetings,

01:03:14.000 --> 01:03:16.000
I knew the technology,

01:03:16.000 --> 01:03:18.000
studied it on purpose.

01:03:18.000 --> 01:03:20.000
Having launched the meeting technology

01:03:20.000 --> 01:03:22.000
for the people who participated in it,

01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:24.000
who held the meeting themselves,

01:03:24.000 --> 01:03:26.000
I was very surprised.

01:03:26.000 --> 01:03:28.000
How surprised?

01:03:28.000 --> 01:03:30.000
First of all,

01:03:30.000 --> 01:03:32.000
since almost everyone has experience

01:03:32.000 --> 01:03:34.000
in holding meetings

01:03:34.000 --> 01:03:36.000
or participation in them,

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:38.000
we will decide what roles there are in the meeting.

01:03:38.000 --> 01:03:40.000
After that, we will try to remove

01:03:40.000 --> 01:03:42.000
the shortcomings that are visible today

01:03:42.000 --> 01:03:44.000
or try to make them a virtue.

01:03:44.000 --> 01:03:46.000
So, when holding a meeting,

01:03:46.000 --> 01:03:48.000
first of all,

01:03:48.000 --> 01:03:50.000
there is

01:03:50.000 --> 01:03:52.000
the role of the chairman,

01:03:52.000 --> 01:03:54.000
the person who leads.

01:03:54.000 --> 01:03:56.000
It does not necessarily mean

01:03:56.000 --> 01:03:58.000
the head of the unit or the whole organization.

01:03:58.000 --> 01:04:00.000
It can be another person

01:04:00.000 --> 01:04:02.000
whom he trusts or entrusts to conduct it.

01:04:02.000 --> 01:04:04.000
There is an organizer of the meeting,

01:04:04.000 --> 01:04:06.000
the person who notifies

01:04:06.000 --> 01:04:08.000
the participants,

01:04:08.000 --> 01:04:10.000
sends them information.

01:04:10.000 --> 01:04:12.000
There is a reporter

01:04:12.000 --> 01:04:14.000
or co-reporters who speak

01:04:14.000 --> 01:04:16.000
with the reporter or co-reporters

01:04:16.000 --> 01:04:18.000
on the previously outlined problems.

01:04:18.000 --> 01:04:20.000
And there are participants

01:04:20.000 --> 01:04:22.000
who listen to the reports

01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:24.000
and make decisions.

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:26.000
Moreover,

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:28.000
it is desirable to have a group of people

01:04:28.000 --> 01:04:30.000
at the meeting

01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:32.000
a little later,

01:04:32.000 --> 01:04:34.000
who are on the so-called

01:04:34.000 --> 01:04:36.000
short leash.

01:04:36.000 --> 01:04:38.000
A person sits at his workplace

01:04:38.000 --> 01:04:40.000
and does his official duties,

01:04:40.000 --> 01:04:42.000
but he knows that at such a time

01:04:42.000 --> 01:04:44.000
he can be invited to a meeting

01:04:44.000 --> 01:04:46.000
on such a question.

01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:48.000
For example, someone in the personnel department

01:04:48.000 --> 01:04:50.000
of the sales organization

01:04:50.000 --> 01:04:52.000
conducts a meeting on the market capture.

01:04:52.000 --> 01:04:54.000
He knows that he can be invited

01:04:54.000 --> 01:04:56.000
on such a question,

01:04:56.000 --> 01:04:58.000
he can do without it.

01:04:58.000 --> 01:05:00.000
He does not go anywhere,

01:05:00.000 --> 01:05:02.000
he does his own business.

01:05:02.000 --> 01:05:04.000
He does not go to other meetings,

01:05:04.000 --> 01:05:06.000
does not go to another organization,

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:08.000
does not meet potential future employees.

01:05:08.000 --> 01:05:10.000
He works with papers,

01:05:10.000 --> 01:05:12.000
he is not distracted by anything.

01:05:12.000 --> 01:05:14.000
Now the question is,

01:05:14.000 --> 01:05:16.000
what is the purpose of the meeting?

01:05:16.000 --> 01:05:18.000
At the meetings,

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:20.000
operational issues are solved,

01:05:20.000 --> 01:05:22.000
which require a creative approach,

01:05:22.000 --> 01:05:24.000
a creative solution.

01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:26.000
And here there is an interesting rule,

01:05:26.000 --> 01:05:28.000
developed over the years abroad,

01:05:28.000 --> 01:05:30.000
that meetings are held

01:05:30.000 --> 01:05:32.000
only when it is impossible

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:34.000
to do without them.

01:05:34.000 --> 01:05:36.000
Here we have,

01:05:36.000 --> 01:05:38.000
as a rule,

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:40.000
especially in administrative structures,

01:05:40.000 --> 01:05:42.000
the so-called meeting of the next plan.

01:05:42.000 --> 01:05:44.000
The head of some units

01:05:44.000 --> 01:05:46.000
is asked to tell them

01:05:46.000 --> 01:05:48.000
what they need to do

01:05:48.000 --> 01:05:50.000
in such an instructive and

01:05:50.000 --> 01:05:52.000
directive manner.

01:05:52.000 --> 01:05:54.000
He asks for reports on what they have done

01:05:54.000 --> 01:05:56.000
and sets new tasks.

01:05:56.000 --> 01:05:58.000
We even have a video

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:00.000
about such meetings

01:06:00.000 --> 01:06:02.000
in Russia.

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:04.000
The question is,

01:06:04.000 --> 01:06:06.000
what are these meetings

01:06:06.000 --> 01:06:08.000
for?

01:06:08.000 --> 01:06:10.000
Let's take an example.

01:06:10.000 --> 01:06:12.000
The governor of the Krasnodar Territory,

01:06:12.000 --> 01:06:14.000
Nikolai Ignatievich Kondratenko,

01:06:14.000 --> 01:06:16.000
used to like to hold

01:06:16.000 --> 01:06:18.000
planning meetings.

01:06:18.000 --> 01:06:20.000
I know how they were held there.

01:06:20.000 --> 01:06:22.000
All heads of local municipalities

01:06:22.000 --> 01:06:24.000
would meet on Mondays

01:06:24.000 --> 01:06:26.000
at 10 or 11 o'clock

01:06:26.000 --> 01:06:28.000
in the Krasnodar Territory administration.

01:06:28.000 --> 01:06:30.000
Someone would drive

01:06:30.000 --> 01:06:32.000
250-300 km,

01:06:32.000 --> 01:06:34.000
and they would come.

01:06:34.000 --> 01:06:36.000
They would spend

01:06:36.000 --> 01:06:38.000
3-4 hours on the road.

01:06:38.000 --> 01:06:40.000
And the governor

01:06:40.000 --> 01:06:42.000
would set tasks for them,

01:06:42.000 --> 01:06:44.000
ask for reports.

01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:46.000
All heads of local municipalities

01:06:46.000 --> 01:06:48.000
would sit with them

01:06:48.000 --> 01:06:50.000
and listen to their tasks,

01:06:50.000 --> 01:06:52.000
their indicators,

01:06:52.000 --> 01:06:54.000
what they had done in the past month,

01:06:54.000 --> 01:06:56.000
what they needed to do, etc.

01:06:56.000 --> 01:06:58.000
I have a question.

01:06:58.000 --> 01:07:00.000
What prevented them

01:07:00.000 --> 01:07:02.000
from sending these tasks

01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:04.000
on the Internet?

01:07:04.000 --> 01:07:06.000
People would sit for 3-4 hours

01:07:06.000 --> 01:07:08.000
and listen to their ideas.

01:07:08.000 --> 01:07:10.000
They did not generate their ideas,

01:07:10.000 --> 01:07:12.000
did not make any proposals.

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:14.000
Why did they go?

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:16.000
After the meeting,

01:07:16.000 --> 01:07:18.000
they would solve their own questions

01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:20.000
with deputies,

01:07:20.000 --> 01:07:22.000
with heads of local municipalities,

01:07:22.000 --> 01:07:24.000
and then go back.

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:26.000
They would spend 3-4 hours on the road.

01:07:26.000 --> 01:07:28.000
They would lose their working day.

01:07:28.000 --> 01:07:30.000
Why?

01:07:30.000 --> 01:07:32.000
It's easy and simple.

01:07:32.000 --> 01:07:34.000
The meeting is held

01:07:34.000 --> 01:07:36.000
when it is necessary to find solutions

01:07:36.000 --> 01:07:38.000
and when it is impossible to do without people's contact.

01:07:38.000 --> 01:07:40.000
There is a so-called

01:07:40.000 --> 01:07:42.000
in-person meeting,

01:07:42.000 --> 01:07:44.000
when information is sent.

01:07:44.000 --> 01:07:46.000
The same report is prepared

01:07:46.000 --> 01:07:48.000
by the reporters.

01:07:48.000 --> 01:07:50.000
The report is prepared by the reporters.

01:07:50.000 --> 01:07:52.000
The internal mail is also sent

01:07:52.000 --> 01:07:54.000
to those people who are interested

01:07:54.000 --> 01:07:56.000
in solving the issue.

01:07:56.000 --> 01:07:58.000
They study it, write their conclusions,

01:07:58.000 --> 01:08:00.000
their proposals, and send it back

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:02.000
to the organizer of the in-person meeting.

01:08:02.000 --> 01:08:04.000
Not to the organization's leader,

01:08:04.000 --> 01:08:06.000
not to his deputy,

01:08:06.000 --> 01:08:08.000
but to the person

01:08:08.000 --> 01:08:10.000
who is preparing the issue.

01:08:10.000 --> 01:08:12.000
The person prepares the issue,

01:08:12.000 --> 01:08:14.000
gets acquainted with the proposals,

01:08:14.000 --> 01:08:16.000
and if it is possible to do without

01:08:16.000 --> 01:08:18.000
the gathering of people,

01:08:18.000 --> 01:08:20.000
without their absence,

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:22.000
then the decision is made

01:08:22.000 --> 01:08:24.000
in person by the person

01:08:24.000 --> 01:08:26.000
who makes the decision,

01:08:26.000 --> 01:08:28.000
by the person who is responsible for it.

01:08:28.000 --> 01:08:30.000
Why is it suggested

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:32.000
to refuse

01:08:32.000 --> 01:08:34.000
the gathering of people

01:08:34.000 --> 01:08:36.000
and the in-person meetings?

01:08:36.000 --> 01:08:38.000
In the end,

01:08:38.000 --> 01:08:40.000
meetings are considered

01:08:40.000 --> 01:08:42.000
the most expensive

01:08:42.000 --> 01:08:44.000
type of management activity in the world.

01:08:44.000 --> 01:08:46.000
Why?

01:08:46.000 --> 01:08:48.000
When I held a meeting

01:08:48.000 --> 01:08:50.000
in this pro-Western organization,

01:08:50.000 --> 01:08:52.000
I sent out a schedule

01:08:52.000 --> 01:08:54.000
and a note at the bottom

01:08:54.000 --> 01:08:56.000
that one minute of our meeting

01:08:56.000 --> 01:08:58.000
costs the same amount

01:08:58.000 --> 01:09:00.000
as the organization.

01:09:00.000 --> 01:09:02.000
Because everyone has their own

01:09:02.000 --> 01:09:04.000
budget for the meeting.

01:09:04.000 --> 01:09:06.000
The leaders usually have high budgets

01:09:06.000 --> 01:09:08.000
with bonuses.

01:09:08.000 --> 01:09:10.000
So, every hour of work

01:09:10.000 --> 01:09:12.000
can be estimated in rubles,

01:09:12.000 --> 01:09:14.000
and every minute, respectively.

01:09:14.000 --> 01:09:16.000
Accordingly,

01:09:16.000 --> 01:09:18.000
the meeting schedule,

01:09:18.000 --> 01:09:20.000
which is recommended

01:09:20.000 --> 01:09:22.000
all over the world,

01:09:22.000 --> 01:09:24.000
was that

01:09:24.000 --> 01:09:26.000
the time for the speaker's speech

01:09:26.000 --> 01:09:28.000
is 2-3 minutes,

01:09:28.000 --> 01:09:30.000
because if the report is already sent out,

01:09:30.000 --> 01:09:32.000
it is easy to go through

01:09:32.000 --> 01:09:34.000
the pain points.

01:09:34.000 --> 01:09:36.000
And the time for the speech

01:09:36.000 --> 01:09:38.000
in the discussions,

01:09:38.000 --> 01:09:40.000
the time for the participants' statements

01:09:40.000 --> 01:09:42.000
is exactly one minute.

01:09:42.000 --> 01:09:44.000
Can you imagine

01:09:44.000 --> 01:09:46.000
the shock

01:09:46.000 --> 01:09:48.000
that the organizer of the meeting

01:09:48.000 --> 01:09:50.000
asked for?

01:09:50.000 --> 01:09:52.000
One minute for a speech?

01:09:52.000 --> 01:09:54.000
How come?

01:09:54.000 --> 01:09:56.000
We are not used to talking like this,

01:09:56.000 --> 01:09:58.000
and when the participants

01:09:58.000 --> 01:10:00.000
of the meeting gathered,

01:10:00.000 --> 01:10:02.000
I explained to him

01:10:02.000 --> 01:10:04.000
why such a strict requirement.

01:10:04.000 --> 01:10:06.000
Generally,

01:10:06.000 --> 01:10:08.000
the normal speech pace

01:10:08.000 --> 01:10:10.000
of a person

01:10:10.000 --> 01:10:12.000
who is perceived by the listener

01:10:12.000 --> 01:10:14.000
is 2 words per second.

01:10:16.000 --> 01:10:18.000
In 60 minutes,

01:10:18.000 --> 01:10:20.000
one can say 120 words.

01:10:22.000 --> 01:10:24.000
If the length of one sentence

01:10:24.000 --> 01:10:26.000
is 4-5-6 words,

01:10:28.000 --> 01:10:30.000
then, accordingly,

01:10:32.000 --> 01:10:34.000
one can say 20 sentences

01:10:34.000 --> 01:10:36.000
in one minute.

01:10:36.000 --> 01:10:38.000
I have a question.

01:10:38.000 --> 01:10:40.000
If a meeting is held

01:10:40.000 --> 01:10:42.000
about a problem

01:10:42.000 --> 01:10:44.000
that could not be solved,

01:10:44.000 --> 01:10:46.000
and suddenly

01:10:46.000 --> 01:10:48.000
a participant of the meeting

01:10:48.000 --> 01:10:50.000
has 20 sentences to solve,

01:10:50.000 --> 01:10:52.000
why is it still not solved?

01:10:54.000 --> 01:10:56.000
The conversation about nothing

01:10:56.000 --> 01:10:58.000
during the meeting

01:10:58.000 --> 01:11:00.000
is expensive for the organization.

01:11:00.000 --> 01:11:02.000
The request was to express

01:11:02.000 --> 01:11:04.000
a proposal to solve the problem.

01:11:04.000 --> 01:11:06.000
I propose to solve the problem

01:11:06.000 --> 01:11:08.000
in this way,

01:11:08.000 --> 01:11:10.000
with the help of such resources.

01:11:10.000 --> 01:11:12.000
This is my request,

01:11:12.000 --> 01:11:14.000
my proposal,

01:11:14.000 --> 01:11:16.000
my limitation on the length

01:11:16.000 --> 01:11:18.000
of the meeting.

01:11:18.000 --> 01:11:20.000
It turns out to be practical

01:11:20.000 --> 01:11:22.000
in the eastern management model.

01:11:22.000 --> 01:11:24.000
The speaker is allowed to speak

01:11:24.000 --> 01:11:26.000
for one minute.

01:11:26.000 --> 01:11:28.000
After one minute,

01:11:28.000 --> 01:11:30.000
the microphone is turned off.

01:11:30.000 --> 01:11:32.000
This is normal.

01:11:32.000 --> 01:11:34.000
This is the custom in the country

01:11:34.000 --> 01:11:36.000
of the rising sun.

01:11:36.000 --> 01:11:38.000
If he continues to speak

01:11:38.000 --> 01:11:40.000
without a microphone,

01:11:40.000 --> 01:11:42.000
he simply goes down

01:11:42.000 --> 01:11:44.000
to the floor with the audience.

01:11:44.000 --> 01:11:46.000
Technically,

01:11:46.000 --> 01:11:48.000
it is impossible to speak

01:11:48.000 --> 01:11:50.000
for more than two minutes.

01:11:50.000 --> 01:11:52.000
This is the custom of the high management culture

01:11:52.000 --> 01:11:54.000
in the east.

01:11:54.000 --> 01:11:56.000
Now the total length

01:11:56.000 --> 01:11:58.000
of the meeting,

01:11:58.000 --> 01:12:00.000
if we hold it from start to finish,

01:12:00.000 --> 01:12:02.000
should be no more than 45 minutes.

01:12:02.000 --> 01:12:04.000
In 45 minutes,

01:12:04.000 --> 01:12:06.000
we need to consider

01:12:06.000 --> 01:12:08.000
the issues on the agenda,

01:12:08.000 --> 01:12:10.000
find the proposed solutions,

01:12:10.000 --> 01:12:12.000
and pass them on to the specialists

01:12:12.000 --> 01:12:14.000
so that they can find

01:12:14.000 --> 01:12:16.000
and justify the resource provision.

01:12:16.000 --> 01:12:18.000
The meetings of 2,

01:12:18.000 --> 01:12:20.000
3, or 4 hours are of no importance

01:12:20.000 --> 01:12:22.000
because a person gets tired

01:12:22.000 --> 01:12:24.000
after 45 minutes,

01:12:24.000 --> 01:12:26.000
and he needs a break.

01:12:26.000 --> 01:12:28.000
Let's look at schools.

01:12:28.000 --> 01:12:30.000
The educational system

01:12:30.000 --> 01:12:32.000
works for 45 minutes worldwide.

01:12:32.000 --> 01:12:34.000
Why? Because a person needs a break.

01:12:34.000 --> 01:12:36.000
The head gets tired of thinking.

01:12:36.000 --> 01:12:38.000
Is it clear?

01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:40.000
Considering these points,

01:12:40.000 --> 01:12:42.000
the speech is within one minute,

01:12:42.000 --> 01:12:44.000
the report is within 2-3 minutes,

01:12:44.000 --> 01:12:46.000
and the length of the meeting is 45 minutes.

01:12:46.000 --> 01:12:48.000
The meeting is held only

01:12:48.000 --> 01:12:50.000
when it is impossible to do without it.

01:12:50.000 --> 01:12:52.000
How many time resources

01:12:52.000 --> 01:12:54.000
will it allow to set up

01:12:54.000 --> 01:12:56.000
an organization in any company

01:12:56.000 --> 01:12:58.000
that will take into account

01:12:58.000 --> 01:13:00.000
the 4 simple rules

01:13:00.000 --> 01:13:02.000
when holding a meeting?

01:13:02.000 --> 01:13:04.000
How much more

01:13:04.000 --> 01:13:06.000
will the employees do their business

01:13:06.000 --> 01:13:08.000
instead of attending meetings

01:13:08.000 --> 01:13:10.000
and often imitating

01:13:10.000 --> 01:13:12.000
their business activity

01:13:12.000 --> 01:13:14.000
at this meeting?

01:13:14.000 --> 01:13:16.000
They may write down a note,

01:13:16.000 --> 01:13:18.000
try to raise their hand,

01:13:18.000 --> 01:13:20.000
throw in a few lines,

01:13:20.000 --> 01:13:22.000
or talk for a long time.

01:13:22.000 --> 01:13:24.000
The next way

01:13:24.000 --> 01:13:26.000
to organize a group work

01:13:26.000 --> 01:13:28.000
is a seminar.

01:13:28.000 --> 01:13:30.000
It is not only

01:13:30.000 --> 01:13:32.000
a seminar,

01:13:32.000 --> 01:13:34.000
but also a way

01:13:34.000 --> 01:13:36.000
to solve a production problem.

01:13:36.000 --> 01:13:38.000
A seminar is not

01:13:38.000 --> 01:13:40.000
a way to solve

01:13:40.000 --> 01:13:42.000
a production problem.

01:13:42.000 --> 01:13:44.000
Unlike meetings,

01:13:44.000 --> 01:13:46.000
it is held much less often

01:13:46.000 --> 01:13:48.000
and is about

01:13:48.000 --> 01:13:50.000
non-urgent problems

01:13:50.000 --> 01:13:52.000
that are more strategic

01:13:52.000 --> 01:13:54.000
than meetings.

01:13:54.000 --> 01:13:56.000
Therefore,

01:13:56.000 --> 01:13:58.000
the seminar preparation time

01:13:58.000 --> 01:14:00.000
is 1.5-2 weeks,

01:14:00.000 --> 01:14:02.000
whereas a meeting

01:14:02.000 --> 01:14:04.000
is 1.5-2 months.

01:14:04.000 --> 01:14:06.000
There are also chairpersons,

01:14:06.000 --> 01:14:08.000
reporters,

01:14:08.000 --> 01:14:10.000
and listeners

01:14:10.000 --> 01:14:12.000
who are interested in solving

01:14:12.000 --> 01:14:14.000
this problem,

01:14:14.000 --> 01:14:16.000
as well as seminar organizers.

01:14:16.000 --> 01:14:18.000
The seminar is different.

01:14:18.000 --> 01:14:20.000
A report is made

01:14:20.000 --> 01:14:22.000
more often

01:14:22.000 --> 01:14:24.000
because the problem is more serious.

01:14:24.000 --> 01:14:26.000
However,

01:14:26.000 --> 01:14:28.000
I think that if people

01:14:28.000 --> 01:14:30.000
are interested in solving a problem,

01:14:30.000 --> 01:14:32.000
they should listen to it.

01:14:32.000 --> 01:14:34.000
If there is something to talk about

01:14:34.000 --> 01:14:36.000
for 15 minutes,

01:14:36.000 --> 01:14:38.000
then it is possible.

01:14:38.000 --> 01:14:40.000
This is my recommendation.

01:14:40.000 --> 01:14:42.000
This is the seminar's approach.

01:14:42.000 --> 01:14:44.000
Unlike meetings,

01:14:44.000 --> 01:14:46.000
the chairperson is recommended

01:14:46.000 --> 01:14:48.000
to organize

01:14:48.000 --> 01:14:50.000
a round of statements

01:14:50.000 --> 01:14:52.000
from participants

01:14:52.000 --> 01:14:54.000
so that everyone

01:14:54.000 --> 01:14:56.000
can speak out

01:14:56.000 --> 01:14:58.000
on the problem

01:14:58.000 --> 01:15:00.000
and its solution.

01:15:00.000 --> 01:15:02.000
First,

01:15:02.000 --> 01:15:04.000
after listening to the painful points,

01:15:04.000 --> 01:15:06.000
then after listening

01:15:06.000 --> 01:15:08.000
to the painful points,

01:15:08.000 --> 01:15:10.000
and then after listening

01:15:10.000 --> 01:15:12.000
to the painful points,

01:15:12.000 --> 01:15:14.000
so that the person can prepare

01:15:14.000 --> 01:15:16.000
in advance for the solution.

01:15:16.000 --> 01:15:18.000
Third,

01:15:18.000 --> 01:15:20.000
his statement should allow

01:15:20.000 --> 01:15:22.000
someone to initiate

01:15:22.000 --> 01:15:24.000
some thoughts.

01:15:24.000 --> 01:15:26.000
What is also common

01:15:26.000 --> 01:15:28.000
in seminars and meetings

01:15:28.000 --> 01:15:30.000
is that both

01:15:30.000 --> 01:15:32.000
are recommended

01:15:32.000 --> 01:15:34.000
to let participants

01:15:34.000 --> 01:15:36.000
stand up

01:15:36.000 --> 01:15:38.000
and walk around

01:15:38.000 --> 01:15:40.000
for 45 minutes.

01:15:40.000 --> 01:15:42.000
Of course, they should not step on the floor

01:15:42.000 --> 01:15:44.000
or knock on the door.

01:15:44.000 --> 01:15:46.000
The room should be cool and cozy

01:15:46.000 --> 01:15:48.000
with mineral water on the tables.

01:15:48.000 --> 01:15:50.000
If participants of the seminar

01:15:50.000 --> 01:15:52.000
are not familiar with each other,

01:15:52.000 --> 01:15:54.000
let alone a large company

01:15:54.000 --> 01:15:56.000
with 10,000 people in the state,

01:15:56.000 --> 01:15:58.000
each participant should have

01:15:58.000 --> 01:16:00.000
a sign with his name and position

01:16:00.000 --> 01:16:02.000
so that they can address each other

01:16:02.000 --> 01:16:04.000
That's all.

01:16:04.000 --> 01:16:06.000
I think it is clear

01:16:06.000 --> 01:16:08.000
how to reduce the time

01:16:08.000 --> 01:16:10.000
to hold a meeting

01:16:10.000 --> 01:16:12.000
and increase their effectiveness.

01:16:12.000 --> 01:16:14.000
Next,

01:16:14.000 --> 01:16:16.000
another way

01:16:16.000 --> 01:16:18.000
of organizing

01:16:18.000 --> 01:16:20.000
a group work

01:16:20.000 --> 01:16:22.000
when adopting

01:16:22.000 --> 01:16:24.000
creative methods

01:16:24.000 --> 01:16:26.000
for governance decisions

01:16:26.000 --> 01:16:28.000
is an expert assessment.

01:16:28.000 --> 01:16:30.000
How is it done?

01:16:30.000 --> 01:16:32.000
Usually,

01:16:32.000 --> 01:16:34.000
10-15 experts

01:16:34.000 --> 01:16:36.000
are enough

01:16:36.000 --> 01:16:38.000
to solve a problem.

01:16:38.000 --> 01:16:40.000
They may not know each other,

01:16:40.000 --> 01:16:42.000
but they are in different organizations.

01:16:42.000 --> 01:16:44.000
It is not necessary

01:16:44.000 --> 01:16:46.000
to be in your own organization.

01:16:46.000 --> 01:16:48.000
They are given a description

01:16:48.000 --> 01:16:50.000
or a report

01:16:50.000 --> 01:16:52.000
of the same person

01:16:52.000 --> 01:16:54.000
who took part in the meeting

01:16:54.000 --> 01:16:56.000
or was supposed to attend the seminar

01:16:56.000 --> 01:16:58.000
but decided to refuse.

01:16:58.000 --> 01:17:00.000
The problem is that

01:17:00.000 --> 01:17:02.000
the experts may be paid,

01:17:02.000 --> 01:17:04.000
free, public, etc.

01:17:04.000 --> 01:17:06.000
Each of them is assessed

01:17:06.000 --> 01:17:08.000
by a certain parameter

01:17:08.000 --> 01:17:10.000
as an expert.

01:17:10.000 --> 01:17:12.000
There are tables and developed methods

01:17:12.000 --> 01:17:14.000
to assess the importance

01:17:14.000 --> 01:17:16.000
of an expert and his decision.

01:17:16.000 --> 01:17:18.000
They work.

01:17:18.000 --> 01:17:20.000
Mathematicians believe

01:17:20.000 --> 01:17:22.000
that it is necessary

01:17:22.000 --> 01:17:24.000
to have a decision

01:17:24.000 --> 01:17:26.000
that is mathematically and statistically

01:17:26.000 --> 01:17:28.000
correct.

01:17:28.000 --> 01:17:30.000
There are more than 100 experts.

01:17:30.000 --> 01:17:32.000
It is hard to achieve this

01:17:32.000 --> 01:17:34.000
in production.

01:17:34.000 --> 01:17:36.000
It is hard to solve

01:17:36.000 --> 01:17:38.000
tactical problems.

01:17:38.000 --> 01:17:40.000
It may not make sense.

01:17:40.000 --> 01:17:42.000
In any case,

01:17:42.000 --> 01:17:44.000
all business processes

01:17:44.000 --> 01:17:46.000
and organization development

01:17:46.000 --> 01:17:48.000
are always a process

01:17:48.000 --> 01:17:50.000
associated with risk

01:17:50.000 --> 01:17:52.000
and a system

01:17:52.000 --> 01:17:54.000
with a large probability

01:17:54.000 --> 01:17:56.000
of uncertainty.

01:17:56.000 --> 01:17:58.000
There may be changes.

01:17:58.000 --> 01:18:00.000
The number of experts

01:18:00.000 --> 01:18:02.000
is not a goal.

01:18:02.000 --> 01:18:04.000
They may read a decision

01:18:04.000 --> 01:18:06.000
and it may be changed

01:18:06.000 --> 01:18:08.000
or not even take place.

01:18:08.000 --> 01:18:10.000
We will talk about

01:18:10.000 --> 01:18:12.000
the necessary decisions

01:18:12.000 --> 01:18:14.000
later.

01:18:14.000 --> 01:18:16.000
Our goal

01:18:16.000 --> 01:18:18.000
is to learn

01:18:18.000 --> 01:18:20.000
to make the right decisions.

01:18:20.000 --> 01:18:22.000
Experts work.

01:18:22.000 --> 01:18:24.000
They develop

01:18:24.000 --> 01:18:26.000
their own criteria

01:18:26.000 --> 01:18:28.000
and recommendations

01:18:28.000 --> 01:18:30.000
on solving problems.

01:18:30.000 --> 01:18:32.000
They submit them to an organizer.

01:18:32.000 --> 01:18:34.000
The working group

01:18:34.000 --> 01:18:36.000
and the organizer

01:18:36.000 --> 01:18:38.000
look at the proposals

01:18:38.000 --> 01:18:40.000
based on the rating

01:18:40.000 --> 01:18:42.000
and importance

01:18:42.000 --> 01:18:44.000
of the experts.

01:18:44.000 --> 01:18:46.000
They also

01:18:46.000 --> 01:18:48.000
provide resources.

01:18:48.000 --> 01:18:50.000
The most important

01:18:50.000 --> 01:18:52.000
and realistic decisions

01:18:52.000 --> 01:18:54.000
are made by the organizer.

01:18:54.000 --> 01:18:56.000
There is another

01:18:56.000 --> 01:18:58.000
interesting way

01:18:58.000 --> 01:19:00.000
of organizing a group

01:19:00.000 --> 01:19:02.000
of people

01:19:02.000 --> 01:19:04.000
who make decisions

01:19:04.000 --> 01:19:06.000
called a business game.

01:19:06.000 --> 01:19:08.000
What is its advantage?

01:19:08.000 --> 01:19:10.000
It has a huge advantage

01:19:10.000 --> 01:19:12.000
compared to other methods.

01:19:12.000 --> 01:19:14.000
Why?

01:19:14.000 --> 01:19:16.000
It not only allows

01:19:16.000 --> 01:19:18.000
to find solutions,

01:19:18.000 --> 01:19:20.000
but also to develop

01:19:20.000 --> 01:19:22.000
the organization.

01:19:22.000 --> 01:19:24.000
First of all,

01:19:24.000 --> 01:19:26.000
it is a training of management skills.

01:19:26.000 --> 01:19:28.000
It is a promotion of

01:19:28.000 --> 01:19:30.000
the participants' skills.

01:19:30.000 --> 01:19:32.000
They learn new approaches

01:19:32.000 --> 01:19:34.000
and develop their cooperation.

01:19:34.000 --> 01:19:36.000
They develop their skills

01:19:36.000 --> 01:19:38.000
to solve similar problems.

01:19:38.000 --> 01:19:40.000
They are used to generating

01:19:40.000 --> 01:19:42.000
new ideas.

01:19:42.000 --> 01:19:44.000
In a business game,

01:19:44.000 --> 01:19:46.000
the group is more active.

01:19:46.000 --> 01:19:48.000
The American model

01:19:48.000 --> 01:19:50.000
of individualistic work

01:19:50.000 --> 01:19:52.000
in the USA

01:19:52.000 --> 01:19:54.000
is based on

01:19:54.000 --> 01:19:56.000
the training of the team.

01:19:56.000 --> 01:19:58.000
The American team

01:19:58.000 --> 01:20:00.000
is trained

01:20:00.000 --> 01:20:02.000
to work as a team.

01:20:02.000 --> 01:20:04.000
Why?

01:20:04.000 --> 01:20:06.000
Because the Americans

01:20:06.000 --> 01:20:08.000
have been learning to work

01:20:08.000 --> 01:20:10.000
individually for two and a half

01:20:10.000 --> 01:20:12.000
hundred years.

01:20:12.000 --> 01:20:14.000
Group decisions are more

01:20:14.000 --> 01:20:16.000
important.

01:20:16.000 --> 01:20:18.000
A business game

01:20:18.000 --> 01:20:20.000
allows to solve a task

01:20:20.000 --> 01:20:22.000
and strengthen a team.

01:20:22.000 --> 01:20:24.000
A manager is not a manager

01:20:24.000 --> 01:20:26.000
until he has a team.

01:20:26.000 --> 01:20:28.000
What are business games?

01:20:28.000 --> 01:20:30.000
They are different.

01:20:30.000 --> 01:20:32.000
A business game has two plans.

01:20:32.000 --> 01:20:34.000
The first one is

01:20:34.000 --> 01:20:36.000
solving a problem.

01:20:36.000 --> 01:20:38.000
The second one is

01:20:38.000 --> 01:20:40.000
training of certain actions.

01:20:40.000 --> 01:20:42.000
The second plan is not

01:20:42.000 --> 01:20:44.000
a business game.

01:20:44.000 --> 01:20:46.000
Only experienced players

01:20:46.000 --> 01:20:48.000
and coaches know

01:20:48.000 --> 01:20:50.000
that there is a plan.

01:20:50.000 --> 01:20:52.000
They try to solve it

01:20:52.000 --> 01:20:54.000
to the maximum.

01:20:54.000 --> 01:20:56.000
Usually, the task is solved,

01:20:56.000 --> 01:20:58.000
but the second plan

01:20:58.000 --> 01:21:00.000
works regardless

01:21:00.000 --> 01:21:02.000
of the organizers' qualifications.

01:21:02.000 --> 01:21:04.000
Business games can be

01:21:04.000 --> 01:21:06.000
imitation, management,

01:21:06.000 --> 01:21:08.000
and so on.

01:21:08.000 --> 01:21:10.000
I have more than

01:21:10.000 --> 01:21:12.000
100 games

01:21:12.000 --> 01:21:14.000
where we make decisions,

01:21:14.000 --> 01:21:16.000
learn management skills,

01:21:16.000 --> 01:21:18.000
learn theoretical questions

01:21:18.000 --> 01:21:20.000
in management,

01:21:20.000 --> 01:21:22.000
such as conflictology,

01:21:22.000 --> 01:21:24.000
organizational structures,

01:21:24.000 --> 01:21:26.000
and at the same time

01:21:26.000 --> 01:21:28.000
solve team formation,

01:21:28.000 --> 01:21:30.000
leadership qualities,

01:21:30.000 --> 01:21:32.000
creative abilities,

01:21:32.000 --> 01:21:34.000
and stress-resistance.

01:21:34.000 --> 01:21:36.000
These are the advantages

01:21:36.000 --> 01:21:38.000
of business games.

01:21:38.000 --> 01:21:40.000
The task is set,

01:21:40.000 --> 01:21:42.000
the participants are informed

01:21:42.000 --> 01:21:44.000
about the task,

01:21:44.000 --> 01:21:46.000
and the game scenario is developed.

01:21:46.000 --> 01:21:48.000
I can't tell you about the scenarios

01:21:48.000 --> 01:21:50.000
because every game

01:21:50.000 --> 01:21:52.000
has its own scenario.

01:21:52.000 --> 01:21:54.000
For example, we know

01:21:54.000 --> 01:21:56.000
the game of the shipwrecked.

01:21:56.000 --> 01:21:58.000
It is a well-known scenario

01:21:58.000 --> 01:22:00.000
where you can lose a lot of situations

01:22:00.000 --> 01:22:02.000
and find solutions.

01:22:02.000 --> 01:22:04.000
In business games,

01:22:04.000 --> 01:22:06.000
the task is

01:22:06.000 --> 01:22:08.000
to make a smooth

01:22:08.000 --> 01:22:10.000
and gradual decision.

01:22:10.000 --> 01:22:12.000
The strongest decisions

01:22:12.000 --> 01:22:14.000
are the ones

01:22:14.000 --> 01:22:16.000
approved by the majority

01:22:16.000 --> 01:22:18.000
of the team.

01:22:18.000 --> 01:22:20.000
In business games,

01:22:20.000 --> 01:22:22.000
unlike seminars

01:22:22.000 --> 01:22:24.000
and expert assessments,

01:22:24.000 --> 01:22:26.000
the task is

01:22:26.000 --> 01:22:28.000
to make a smooth

01:22:28.000 --> 01:22:30.000
and gradual decision.

01:22:30.000 --> 01:22:32.000
The task is to make a smooth

01:22:32.000 --> 01:22:34.000
and gradual decision.

01:22:34.000 --> 01:22:36.000
Unlike seminars and expert assessments,

01:22:36.000 --> 01:22:38.000
meetings and brainstorming

01:22:38.000 --> 01:22:40.000
allow to bring

01:22:40.000 --> 01:22:42.000
the entire team

01:22:42.000 --> 01:22:44.000
to the solution of the problem.

01:22:44.000 --> 01:22:46.000
You can organize

01:22:46.000 --> 01:22:48.000
the game scenario

01:22:48.000 --> 01:22:50.000
on the lower levels

01:22:50.000 --> 01:22:52.000
where each specialist

01:22:52.000 --> 01:22:54.000
and team member

01:22:54.000 --> 01:22:56.000
make a general decision

01:22:56.000 --> 01:22:58.000
and then the decision

01:22:58.000 --> 01:23:00.000
is transferred to another level

01:23:00.000 --> 01:23:02.000
of the first line managers.

01:23:02.000 --> 01:23:04.000
The decision is processed

01:23:04.000 --> 01:23:06.000
in the same way

01:23:06.000 --> 01:23:08.000
as the first line managers

01:23:08.000 --> 01:23:10.000
process the ideas

01:23:10.000 --> 01:23:12.000
that were proposed

01:23:12.000 --> 01:23:14.000
from the specialists' level.

01:23:14.000 --> 01:23:16.000
The decisions are processed,

01:23:16.000 --> 01:23:18.000
the approaches are developed,

01:23:18.000 --> 01:23:20.000
they are strengthened

01:23:20.000 --> 01:23:22.000
and transferred to the middle level.

01:23:22.000 --> 01:23:24.000
The middle level is again

01:23:24.000 --> 01:23:26.000
divided into 2-3 groups

01:23:26.000 --> 01:23:28.000
and each group makes improvements

01:23:28.000 --> 01:23:30.000
and strengthens the decisions

01:23:30.000 --> 01:23:32.000
so that each member of the team

01:23:32.000 --> 01:23:34.000
and each organization

01:23:34.000 --> 01:23:36.000
becomes involved

01:23:36.000 --> 01:23:38.000
in the decision

01:23:38.000 --> 01:23:40.000
that is made

01:23:40.000 --> 01:23:42.000
at the top level.

01:23:42.000 --> 01:23:44.000
The first line managers

01:23:44.000 --> 01:23:46.000
and specialists

01:23:46.000 --> 01:23:48.000
are involved in the business game

01:23:48.000 --> 01:23:50.000
and in the game form.

01:23:50.000 --> 01:23:52.000
What is the advantage of the game form?

01:23:52.000 --> 01:23:54.000
People do not offend each other.

01:23:54.000 --> 01:23:56.000
They play.

01:23:56.000 --> 01:23:58.000
If someone outplayed someone,

01:23:58.000 --> 01:24:00.000
it is a game.

01:24:00.000 --> 01:24:02.000
Why should you be offended

01:24:02.000 --> 01:24:04.000
if he is stronger?

01:24:04.000 --> 01:24:06.000
We do not really get offended

01:24:06.000 --> 01:24:08.000
when we play volleyball

01:24:08.000 --> 01:24:10.000
team against team.

01:24:10.000 --> 01:24:12.000
Unlike meetings,

01:24:12.000 --> 01:24:14.000
if a decision has been made,

01:24:14.000 --> 01:24:16.000
an alternative figure

01:24:16.000 --> 01:24:18.000
and decision-maker

01:24:18.000 --> 01:24:20.000
can be offended.

01:24:20.000 --> 01:24:22.000
I proposed a decision

01:24:22.000 --> 01:24:24.000
that is better than that.

01:24:24.000 --> 01:24:26.000
My decision is always better

01:24:26.000 --> 01:24:28.000
than that decision.

01:24:28.000 --> 01:24:30.000
It is a shame on the management

01:24:30.000 --> 01:24:32.000
and on the person who came up with the decision.

01:24:32.000 --> 01:24:34.000
In the game,

01:24:34.000 --> 01:24:36.000
it is difficult to offend

01:24:36.000 --> 01:24:38.000
your colleagues

01:24:38.000 --> 01:24:40.000
because the decisions are collegial.

01:24:40.000 --> 01:24:42.000
Secondly, they are getting stronger

01:24:42.000 --> 01:24:44.000
and stronger.

01:24:44.000 --> 01:24:46.000
Even if someone's decision

01:24:46.000 --> 01:24:48.000
did not pass,

01:24:48.000 --> 01:24:50.000
it is a game.

01:24:50.000 --> 01:24:52.000
It is a psychological atmosphere

01:24:52.000 --> 01:24:54.000
of trust and comfort.

01:24:54.000 --> 01:24:56.000
It is better to make decisions

01:24:56.000 --> 01:24:58.000
through business games

01:24:58.000 --> 01:25:00.000
than through meetings and seminars.
